text: Rosiane Modesto de Oliveira (born February 20, 1978) is a Brazilian politician and teacher. She served as federal representative for the state of Mato Grosso do Sul from 2019 to 2023. She served as deputy governor of Mato Grosso do Sul in the government of Reinaldo Azambuja from January 2015 to January 2019. From January 2015 to April 2016, she served as Minister of Human Rights, Social Assistance and Labor for the state of Mato Grosso do Sul during the government of Reinaldo Azambuja. == References == Category:1978 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Mato Grosso do Sul Category:Teachers
